{
  "_id": "OrDBgS5M8Dg7t4eu",
  "name": "Servitor of Spirits (Tian Xia*)",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/environment/settlement/watchtower-city.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl340_LabelType\">For as long as you can remember, the spirits have always whispered into your ears and guided you&mdash;provided that you appease them.</span></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTraits_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl340_LabelType\">Must hail from Tian Xia or have lived there for at least 1 year</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl340_LabelType\">At the start of each day, you can choose one medium spirit (<em>Pathfinder RPG Occult Adventures 33&ndash;36</em>) and accept one of its taboos for 24 hours. As long as you don&rsquo;t break that taboo, once during the next 24 hours, you can add a +1 trait bonus to any one roll, check, or saving throw (but not to AC) listed under your chosen spirit&rsquo;s spirit bonus. Using this ability is a free action that you can use even if it isn&rsquo;t your turn. If you are a medium, the spirit you choose with this trait must be the same as the spirit you are channeling and vice versa.</span></p>",
